<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Task 1 — What are the Jewish Marks of Faith?</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,500;0,700;1,500&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,600;1,300;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root {
  --navy: #0f2235;
  --navy-mid: #1a3a5c;
  --gold: #c49a2a;
  --gold-lt: #e8c060;
  --gold-pale: #fdf6e3;
  --cream: #faf7f0;
  --cream-d: #ede8da;
  --ink: #1c1208;
  --ink-mid: #4a3c22;
  --ink-lt: #7a6a4a;
  --blue-bg: #eef3fa;
  --amber-bg: #fff8ee;
  --green: #1e5c38;
  --green-bg: #edf7f1;
  --red: #7a1f1f;
  --red-bg: #fdf0f0;
  --r: 12px;
}
*,*::before,*::after{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
body{font-family:'Source Serif 4',serif;background:var(--cream);color:var(--ink);min-height:100vh;font-size:16.5px;line-height:1.7}

/* ── TOP BAR ── */
.topbar{background:var(--navy);padding:10px 28px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;position:sticky;top:0;z-index:100;box-shadow:0 2px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.35)}
.topbar-left{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px}
.topbar-star{color:var(--gold-lt);font-size:1.3rem;filter:drop-shadow(0 0 6px rgba(228,192,96,.5))}
.topbar-title{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:#fff;font-size:.95rem}
.topbar-title span{color:var(--gold-lt)}
.timer-badge{background:rgba(196,154,42,.18);border:1px solid rgba(196,154,42,.4);color:var(--gold-lt);padding:4px 12px;border-radius:20px;font-size:.8rem;letter-spacing:.5px}

/* ── HERO ── */
.hero{background:linear-gradient(150deg,var(--navy) 0%,#1a3a5c 60%,#0d2040 100%);padding:52px 28px 44px;text-align:center;position:relative;overflow:hidden}
.hero::after{content:'✡';position:absolute;right:6%;top:50%;transform:translateY(-50%);font-size:9rem;opacity:.05;color:var(--gold-lt)}
.hero-badge{display:inline-block;background:rgba(196,154,42,.18);border:1px solid rgba(196,154,42,.4);color:var(--gold-lt);font-size:.75rem;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;padding:5px 14px;border-radius:20px;margin-bottom:16px}
.hero h1{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:clamp(1.9rem,5vw,2.8rem);color:#fff;line-height:1.15;margin-bottom:10px}
.hero h1 em{color:var(--gold-lt);font-style:italic}
.hero-sub{color:rgba(255,255,255,.6);font-size:.88rem;letter-spacing:1.5px;text-transform:uppercase}

/* ── MAIN ── */
main{max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding:40px 24px 80px}

/* ── SECTION HEADERS ── */
.sec-label{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;background:var(--navy-mid);color:var(--gold-lt);font-size:.72rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:2px;text-transform:uppercase;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:20px;margin-bottom:10px}
.sec-title{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.45rem;color:var(--ink);margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.25}
.sec-intro{color:var(--ink-mid);margin-bottom:24px;font-size:.95rem;padding-left:14px;border-left:3px solid var(--gold)}

/* ── INFO BOX ── */
.info-box{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--cream-d);border-radius:var(--r);padding:22px 26px;margin-bottom:20px;box-shadow:0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,.06)}
.info-box h3{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--navy-mid);margin-bottom:8px}
.info-box p{font-size:.93rem;color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.65}
.info-box ul{padding-left:18px;margin-top:8px}
.info-box li{font-size:.93rem;color:var(--ink-mid);margin-bottom:4px}

/* ── 3 PILLARS ── */
.pillars{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin:24px 0}
@media(max-width:580px){.pillars{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.pillar{border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px 16px;text-align:center}
.pillar.belief{background:var(--blue-bg);border:2px solid #3060a0}
.pillar.action{background:var(--amber-bg);border:2px solid #d47000}
.pillar.symbol{background:var(--green-bg);border:2px solid var(--green)}
.pillar-icon{font-size:2rem;margin-bottom:8px;display:block}
.pillar h3{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:.95rem;margin-bottom:6px}
.pillar.belief h3{color:#1a3a8a}
.pillar.action h3{color:#8a4800}
.pillar.symbol h3{color:var(--green)}
.pillar p{font-size:.8rem;color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.45}

/* ── DIVIDER ── */
.divider{border:none;border-top:1px solid var(--cream-d);margin:36px 0}
.divider-star{text-align:center;color:rgba(196,154,42,.5);letter-spacing:10px;font-size:1rem;margin:32px 0}

/* ── ACTIVITY LABEL ── */
.activity-label{background:var(--gold);color:#fff;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;font-size:.75rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:1.5px;text-transform:uppercase;padding:4px 12px;border-radius:6px;margin-bottom:14px}

/* ─── ACTIVITY A: Match definitions ─── */
.match-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:14px;margin-bottom:20px}
@media(max-width:580px){.match-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.match-left,.match-right{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px}
.match-term{background:var(--navy);color:#fff;padding:11px 16px;border-radius:8px;font-size:.88rem;font-weight:600;text-align:center;user-select:none;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;border:2px solid transparent}
.match-term:hover,.match-term.selected{border-color:var(--gold-lt);background:var(--navy-mid)}
.match-term.matched{background:var(--green);border-color:#5dbb88;cursor:default}
.match-term.wrong-flash{background:var(--red);border-color:#e55;animation:shake .3s ease}
.match-def{background:#fff;border:2px solid var(--cream-d);padding:11px 16px;border-radius:8px;font-size:.84rem;color:var(--ink-mid);cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;line-height:1.4}
.match-def:hover,.match-def.selected{border-color:var(--gold);background:var(--gold-pale)}
.match-def.matched{border-color:var(--green);background:var(--green-bg);cursor:default}
.match-def.wrong-flash{border-color:var(--red);background:var(--red-bg);animation:shake .3s ease}
@keyframes shake{0%,100%{transform:translateX(0)}25%{transform:translateX(-5px)}75%{transform:translateX(5px)}}
.match-score{text-align:center;font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy-mid);font-size:.95rem;margin-top:6px;min-height:28px}

/* ─── ACTIVITY B: Fill in blanks ─── */
.fill-para{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--cream-d);border-radius:var(--r);padding:22px 26px;margin-bottom:16px;font-size:.93rem;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.9;box-shadow:0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.05)}
.blank{display:inline-block;border-bottom:2px solid var(--gold);min-width:110px;text-align:center;padding:0 4px;color:transparent;background:var(--gold-pale);border-radius:4px;font-weight:600;cursor:default;transition:all .3s;position:relative}
.blank.revealed{color:var(--navy);background:var(--blue-bg);border-color:var(--navy-mid)}
.blank.wrong{background:var(--red-bg);border-color:var(--red);color:var(--red)}
.fill-options{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:18px}
.fill-chip{padding:8px 16px;border:2px solid var(--cream-d);border-radius:20px;background:#fff;font-size:.88rem;color:var(--ink-mid);cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;user-select:none}
.fill-chip:hover{border-color:var(--gold);background:var(--gold-pale);color:var(--ink)}
.fill-chip.used{opacity:.35;pointer-events:none;text-decoration:line-through}
.fill-chip.selected{border-color:var(--navy);background:var(--navy);color:#fff}

/* ─── ACTIVITY C: DRAG & DROP ─── */
.bank-label{font-size:.78rem;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;color:var(--ink-lt);margin-bottom:8px}
.cards-bank{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;min-height:52px;padding:10px;background:var(--cream-d);border:2px dashed rgba(196,154,42,.4);border-radius:var(--r);margin-bottom:22px}
.sort-card{padding:9px 14px;background:var(--navy);color:#fff;border-radius:7px;font-size:.82rem;cursor:grab;line-height:1.4;transition:transform .15s,box-shadow .15s,opacity .15s;user-select:none;border:1px solid rgba(228,192,96,.2)}
.sort-card:hover{transform:scale(1.03);box-shadow:0 4px 14px rgba(0,0,0,.25)}
.sort-card:active{cursor:grabbing}
.sort-card.correct-slot{background:var(--green);border-color:#5dbb88}
.sort-card.wrong-slot{background:var(--red);border-color:#d05}
.sort-cols{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;margin-bottom:18px}
@media(max-width:600px){.sort-cols{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sort-col h4{text-align:center;padding:8px;border-radius:6px;font-size:.85rem;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px;letter-spacing:.5px}
.sort-col.bel h4{background:#1a3a8a;color:#fff}
.sort-col.act h4{background:#d47000;color:#fff}
.sort-col.sym h4{background:var(--green);color:#fff}
.drop-zone{min-height:100px;border:2px dashed #ccc;border-radius:8px;padding:8px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;transition:border-color .2s,background .2s}
.drop-zone.over{border-color:var(--gold);background:var(--gold-pale)}
.sort-col.bel .drop-zone{background:var(--blue-bg);border-color:rgba(48,96,160,.3)}
.sort-col.act .drop-zone{background:var(--amber-bg);border-color:rgba(212,112,0,.3)}
.sort-col.sym .drop-zone{background:var(--green-bg);border-color:rgba(30,92,56,.3)}
.sort-result{text-align:center;font-size:.9rem;padding:12px;border-radius:8px;display:none;margin-top:4px}

/* ─── ACTIVITY D: Spot the wrong word ─── */
.wrong-word-block{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--cream-d);border-radius:var(--r);padding:20px 24px;margin-bottom:14px;box-shadow:0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.05)}
.wrong-word-block p{font-size:.93rem;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.8}
.wrong-word{background:#fdecea;color:var(--red);border-bottom:2px dashed var(--red);border-radius:3px;padding:1px 4px;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;font-weight:600}
.wrong-word:hover{background:var(--red);color:#fff}
.wrong-word.found{background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green);border-color:var(--green);cursor:default}
.wrong-word.missed{background:var(--red-bg);outline:2px solid var(--red)}
.correct-word{background:var(--green-bg);color:var(--green);border-radius:3px;padding:1px 5px;font-weight:600;display:none}
.wrong-word.found + .correct-word{display:inline}
.ww-feedback{font-size:.83rem;color:var(--ink-mid);margin-top:8px;display:none}

/* ─── BUTTONS ─── */
.btn{padding:11px 24px;border:none;border-radius:8px;font-family:'Source Serif 4',serif;font-size:.93rem;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;letter-spacing:.3px}
.btn-gold{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--gold),var(--gold-lt));color:var(--ink);box-shadow:0 3px 14px rgba(196,154,42,.35)}
.btn-gold:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);box-shadow:0 7px 20px rgba(196,154,42,.45)}
.btn-ghost{background:var(--cream-d);color:var(--ink-mid)}
.btn-ghost:hover{background:#ddd5c0}
.btn-navy{background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--navy),var(--navy-mid));color:#fff;box-shadow:0 3px 14px rgba(15,34,53,.3)}
.btn-navy:hover{transform:translateY(-2px)}
.btn-row{display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:18px}

/* ─── PROGRESS STRIP ─── */
.progress-strip{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:32px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--cream-d);border-radius:var(--r);padding:14px 18px;box-shadow:0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.05)}
.prog-step{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;font-size:.8rem;color:var(--ink-lt)}
.prog-step .dot{width:22px;height:22px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--cream-d);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:.7rem;font-weight:700;transition:all .3s}
.prog-step.done .dot{background:var(--gold);color:#fff}
.prog-sep{flex:1;height:2px;background:var(--cream-d);border-radius:2px}

/* ─── ANSWER REVEAL ─── */
.reveal-btn{background:none;border:1px solid var(--cream-d);color:var(--ink-lt);padding:7px 14px;border-radius:6px;font-size:.8rem;cursor:pointer;transition:all .2s;margin-top:10px;font-family:'Source Serif 4',serif}
.reveal-btn:hover{border-color:var(--gold);color:var(--gold)}
.reveal-box{display:none;background:var(--gold-pale);border:1px solid rgba(196,154,42,.35);border-radius:8px;padding:14px 18px;margin-top:10px;font-size:.87rem;color:var(--ink-mid);line-height:1.65}
.reveal-box.open{display:block;animation:fadeIn .25s ease}
.reveal-box ul{padding-left:16px}
.reveal-box li{margin-bottom:4px}
.reveal-box strong{color:var(--ink)}

/* ─── FINISH BANNER ─── */
.finish-banner{display:none;background:linear-gradient(135deg,var(--navy) 0%,#1a3a5c 100%);border-radius:var(--r);padding:30px;text-align:center;margin-top:32px;box-shadow:0 8px 36px rgba(0,0,0,.2)}
.finish-banner.show{display:block;animation:fadeIn .5s ease}
.finish-banner .big{font-size:2.8rem;display:block;margin-bottom:12px;filter:drop-shadow(0 0 10px rgba(228,192,96,.6))}
.finish-banner h2{font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--gold-lt);font-size:1.5rem;margin-bottom:8px}
.finish-banner p{color:rgba(255,255,255,.7);font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:6px}
.finish-banner a{display:inline-block;margin-top:16px;background:var(--gold);color:var(--ink);padding:11px 26px;border-radius:8px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;font-size:.92rem;transition:all .2s}
.finish-banner a:hover{background:var(--gold-lt);transform:translateY(-2px)}

@keyframes fadeIn{from{opacity:0;transform:translateY(8px)}to{opacity:1;transform:none}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="topbar">
  <div class="topbar-left">
    <span class="topbar-star">✡</span>
    <span class="topbar-title">Jewish Marks of Faith · <span>Task 1 of 4</span></span>
  </div>
  <span class="timer-badge">⏱ 5–10 min</span>
</div>

<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-badge">Year 8 · Unit 4 · Lesson 3</div>
  <h1>What are the <em>Marks of Faith?</em></h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">Belief · Action · Symbol</p>
</div>

<main>

  <!-- Progress -->
  <div class="progress-strip">
    <div class="prog-step" id="ps1"><div class="dot" id="pd1">A</div><span>Match</span></div>
    <div class="prog-sep"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="ps2"><div class="dot" id="pd2">B</div><span>Fill Blanks</span></div>
    <div class="prog-sep"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="ps3"><div class="dot" id="pd3">C</div><span>Sorting</span></div>
    <div class="prog-sep"></div>
    <div class="prog-step" id="ps4"><div class="dot" id="pd4">D</div><span>Spot Error</span></div>
  </div>

  <!-- INTRO -->
  <div class="sec-label">📖 Introduction</div>
  <h2 class="sec-title">What is a "Mark of Faith"?</h2>
  <p class="sec-intro">Being part of a religion isn't just about one thing. In Judaism, identity is made up of three overlapping categories. Read the explanations, then work through the four activities below.</p>

  <div class="pillars">
    <div class="pillar belief">
      <span class="pillar-icon">💭</span>
      <h3>Beliefs</h3>
      <p><strong>Internal / Thoughts</strong> — private values and ideas held in the mind or heart, such as believing in one G-d.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar action">
      <span class="pillar-icon">🙌</span>
      <h3>Actions</h3>
      <p><strong>Doing / Practices</strong> — things people do to live out their beliefs, such as keeping Shabbat or giving Tzedakah.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar symbol">
      <span class="pillar-icon">👁️</span>
      <h3>Symbols</h3>
      <p><strong>Seeing / Objects</strong> — visible objects worn or displayed, such as the Kippah or Magen David.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="info-box">
    <h3>📌 Key note: Why write "G-d"?</h3>
    <p>You will see "G-d" written throughout this lesson. This is intentional — many Jewish people avoid writing the full name of God to prevent it from ever being erased or defaced, which would be considered disrespectful.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider-star">✦ ✡ ✦</div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════
       ACTIVITY A — MATCH IT UP
  ══════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="activity-label">🔗 Activity A — Match the Term to its Definition</div>
  <h2 class="sec-title">Match the Jewish Terms</h2>
  <p class="sec-intro">Click a term on the left, then click its matching definition on the right. All six must be matched correctly to complete the activity.</p>

  <div class="match-grid">
    <div class="match-left">
      <div class="match-term" data-id="shema" onclick="pickTerm(this)">Shema</div>
      <div class="match-term" data-id="kippah" onclick="pickTerm(this)">Kippah</div>
      <div class="match-term" data-id="shabbat" onclick="pickTerm(this)">Shabbat</div>
      <div class="match-term" data-id="tikkun" onclick="pickTerm(this)">Tikkun Olam</div>
      <div class="match-term" data-id="mezuzah" onclick="pickTerm(this)">Mezuzah</div>
      <div class="match-term" data-id="tzedakah" onclick="pickTerm(this)">Tzedakah</div>
    </div>
    <div class="match-right">
      <div class="match-def" data-id="tikkun" onclick="pickDef(this)">The belief that Jews have a responsibility to repair the world through acts of justice and kindness.</div>
      <div class="match-def" data-id="mezuzah" onclick="pickDef(this)">A small case fixed to the doorpost of a Jewish home, containing a scroll with the Shema written on it.</div>
      <div class="match-def" data-id="shema" onclick="pickDef(this)">The central prayer of Jewish faith affirming that G-d is One; recited morning and evening.</div>
      <div class="match-def" data-id="tzedakah" onclick="pickDef(this)">Often translated as "charity" but more accurately means "justice" — a religious obligation to help those in need.</div>
      <div class="match-def" data-id="kippah" onclick="pickDef(this)">A skullcap worn to show reverence for G-d — a visible symbol of Jewish identity.</div>
      <div class="match-def" data-id="shabbat" onclick="pickDef(this)">The Jewish day of rest, from Friday evening to Saturday evening — a weekly commanded pause from work.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="match-score" id="matchScore"></div>

  <div class="divider-star">✦ ✡ ✦</div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════
       ACTIVITY B — FILL IN BLANKS
  ══════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="activity-label">✏️ Activity B — Fill in the Blanks</div>
  <h2 class="sec-title">Complete the Paragraph</h2>
  <p class="sec-intro">Select a word from the options below, then click on a blank to fill it in. Use each word only once.</p>

  <div class="fill-options" id="fillBank">
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="monotheism" onclick="selectChip(this)">monotheism</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="actions" onclick="selectChip(this)">actions</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="symbols" onclick="selectChip(this)">symbols</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="beliefs" onclick="selectChip(this)">beliefs</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="Shabbat" onclick="selectChip(this)">Shabbat</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="Mezuzah" onclick="selectChip(this)">Mezuzah</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="kosher" onclick="selectChip(this)">kosher</div>
    <div class="fill-chip" data-word="Kippah" onclick="selectChip(this)">Kippah</div>
  </div>

  <div class="fill-para">
    In Judaism, identity is expressed through three marks of faith: <span class="blank" data-answer="beliefs" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span>, <span class="blank" data-answer="actions" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span>, and <span class="blank" data-answer="symbols" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span>. Beliefs are internal — they are thoughts held in the heart. The most fundamental Jewish belief is <span class="blank" data-answer="monotheism" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span>, the idea that there is only one G-d. Actions are the practices people carry out to live out those beliefs. For example, keeping <span class="blank" data-answer="Shabbat" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span> — the weekly day of rest — and eating only <span class="blank" data-answer="kosher" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span> food are both important actions in Jewish life. Symbols are visible objects. The <span class="blank" data-answer="Kippah" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span> is a skullcap worn to show reverence for G-d, while the <span class="blank" data-answer="Mezuzah" onclick="placeWord(this)">________</span> is a case on the doorpost that holds a scroll with the Shema prayer inside.
  </div>

  <div class="btn-row">
    <button class="btn btn-gold" onclick="checkFill()">✦ Check Answers</button>
    <button class="btn btn-ghost" onclick="resetFill()">↺ Reset</button>
  </div>
  <div id="fillFeedback" style="margin-top:12px;font-size:.88rem;display:none;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:8px;"></div>

  <div class="divider-star">✦ ✡ ✦</div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════
       ACTIVITY C — SORT IT
  ══════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="activity-label">🔀 Activity C — Drag & Drop Sorting</div>
  <h2 class="sec-title">Belief, Action, or Symbol?</h2>
  <p class="sec-intro">Drag each card into the correct column. Some items could fit more than one — place them where they best belong.</p>

  <p class="bank-label">Cards to sort:</p>
  <div class="cards-bank" id="sortBank"
    ondrop="sDrop(event,'bank')" ondragover="sOver(event)" ondragleave="sLeave(event)">
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="a" data-correct="bel">Belief in one G-d (Monotheism)</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="b" data-correct="act">Keeping Shabbat — weekly rest</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="c" data-correct="sym">Magen David (Star of David)</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="d" data-correct="bel">Tikkun Olam — repairing the world</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="e" data-correct="act">Giving Tzedakah (charity)</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="f" data-correct="sym">Kippah (skullcap)</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="g" data-correct="act">Eating kosher food</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="h" data-correct="sym">Mezuzah on the doorpost</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="i" data-correct="bel">Future hope — belief in a coming time of peace</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="j" data-correct="act">Praying three times a day</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="k" data-correct="act">Studying the Torah</div>
    <div class="sort-card" draggable="true" ondragstart="sStart(event)" data-id="l" data-correct="sym">Hebrew writing on religious objects</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sort-cols">
    <div class="sort-col bel">
      <h4>💭 Belief</h4>
      <div class="drop-zone" id="zone-bel" ondrop="sDrop(event,'bel')" ondragover="sOver(event)" ondragleave="sLeave(event)"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="sort-col act">
      <h4>🙌 Action</h4>
      <div class="drop-zone" id="zone-act" ondrop="sDrop(event,'act')" ondragover="sOver(event)" ondragleave="sLeave(event)"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="sort-col sym">
      <h4>👁️ Symbol</h4>
      <div class="drop-zone" id="zone-sym" ondrop="sDrop(event,'sym')" ondragover="sOver(event)" ondragleave="sLeave(event)"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sort-result" id="sortResult"></div>

  <div class="btn-row">
    <button class="btn btn-gold" onclick="checkSort()">✦ Check Sorting</button>
    <button class="btn btn-ghost" onclick="resetSort()">↺ Reset</button>
  </div>

  <button class="reveal-btn" onclick="toggleReveal('sortKey')">🔑 Show answer key</button>
  <div class="reveal-box" id="sortKey">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Beliefs:</strong> Monotheism · Tikkun Olam · Future hope</li>
      <li><strong>Actions:</strong> Shabbat · Tzedakah · Kosher · Prayer · Studying Torah</li>
      <li><strong>Symbols:</strong> Magen David · Kippah · Mezuzah · Hebrew writing</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:8px;font-style:italic;font-size:.83rem;">Note: some items, especially the Shema and Tefillin, bridge more than one category — you'll explore this in Task 2.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider-star">✦ ✡ ✦</div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════
       ACTIVITY D — WRONG WORD
  ══════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="activity-label">🔍 Activity D — Spot the Wrong Word</div>
  <h2 class="sec-title">Correct the Mistake</h2>
  <p class="sec-intro">Each sentence below contains one incorrect word shown in red. Click on it to reveal the correction and why it matters.</p>

  <div class="wrong-word-block">
    <p>The <span class="wrong-word" data-correct="Kippah" data-explain="The Kippah (skullcap) is the visible symbol. The Tefillin is worn during prayer but serves a different purpose." onclick="foundWW(this)">Tefillin</span><span class="correct-word"> → Kippah</span> is a skullcap worn on the head to show reverence for G-d above.</p>
    <div class="ww-feedback" id="ww1">✅ The <strong>Kippah</strong> is the skullcap. Tefillin are the leather boxes worn on the arm and forehead during prayer — a different object entirely.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="wrong-word-block">
    <p>Shabbat is the Jewish day of rest, observed from <span class="wrong-word" data-correct="Friday" data-explain="Shabbat begins at Friday evening (sunset), not Saturday." onclick="foundWW(this)">Saturday</span><span class="correct-word"> → Friday</span> evening to Saturday evening.</p>
    <div class="ww-feedback" id="ww2">✅ Shabbat begins on <strong>Friday evening</strong> at sunset and ends on Saturday at nightfall — a full 25 hours of rest.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="wrong-word-block">
    <p>Tzedakah is often translated as "charity," but the Hebrew root actually means <span class="wrong-word" data-correct="justice" data-explain="The root 'Tzedek' means justice or righteousness — giving to the poor is a duty, not a generous extra." onclick="foundWW(this)">generosity</span><span class="correct-word"> → justice</span>.</p>
    <div class="ww-feedback" id="ww3">✅ "Tzedek" means <strong>justice</strong> or righteousness. Tzedakah is a religious obligation — helping others is not just kind, it is required.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="wrong-word-block">
    <p>The Mezuzah is placed on the <span class="wrong-word" data-correct="doorpost" data-explain="The Mezuzah goes on the doorpost (frame), not the window. This fulfils the commandment in the Shema." onclick="foundWW(this)">window</span><span class="correct-word"> → doorpost</span> of a Jewish home, containing the Shema on a small scroll.</p>
    <div class="ww-feedback" id="ww4">✅ The Mezuzah is fixed to the <strong>doorpost</strong> — fulfilling the Shema's instruction to "write them on the doorposts of your house."</div>
  </div>

  <div class="wrong-word-block">
    <p>Kosher food rules include: no <span class="wrong-word" data-correct="pork" data-explain="Pork and shellfish are both forbidden, but pork is the most commonly cited example in Jewish dietary law." onclick="foundWW(this)">beef</span><span class="correct-word"> → pork</span>, no shellfish, and never mixing meat and milk in the same meal.</p>
    <div class="ww-feedback" id="ww5">✅ <strong>Beef</strong> is permitted under kosher law. It is <strong>pork</strong> and shellfish that are forbidden, along with the mixing of meat and dairy.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="btn-row">
    <button class="btn btn-gold" onclick="checkAllWW()">✦ Check All Corrections</button>
  </div>
  <div id="wwFeedback" style="margin-top:10px;font-size:.88rem;display:none;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:8px;"></div>

  <!-- FINISH -->
  <div class="finish-banner" id="finishBanner">
    <span class="big">✡</span>
    <h2>Task 1 Complete!</h2>
    <p>You've matched key terms, filled in the blanks, sorted marks of faith, and spotted errors — great work!</p>
    <p style="margin-top:6px;">Next: <strong>Task 2</strong> focuses on the Shema prayer and how it connects all three marks of faith.</p>
